name: Starliner return
summary: Boeing's Starliner spacecraft successfully returned to Earth from the International Space Station (ISS) on Friday. The spacecraft, which was uncrewed, performed as expected and landed smoothly in the desert of New Mexico. The mission marked the completion of a key milestone in Boeing's efforts to develop a commercial crew transportation system for NASA. The Starliner spacecraft is designed to carry astronauts to and from the ISS, and it is expected to play a significant role in future space exploration missions.

name: Sergio Mendes
summary: Brazilian music legend Sérgio Mendes, known for his innovative fusion of bossa nova with pop and jazz, has passed away at the age of 83. Mendes played a vital role in popularizing Brazilian rhythms on the global stage through his band Brasil '66. His unique sound, which blended traditional Brazilian melodies with elements of American pop and jazz, won him international acclaim and numerous awards, including a Grammy Award. Mendes' legacy as a music innovator and ambassador of Brazilian culture continues to inspire and influence musicians worldwide.

summary: Michael Keaton, star of the upcoming "Beetlejuice Beetlejuice" sequel, is considering using his real name, Michael Douglas, professionally. The actor has been earning praise for his performance in the new film, which marks his return to the beloved character 35 years after the original "Beetlejuice." Keaton has also been reflecting on his favorite scenes from the first movie, sharing his thoughts with USA TODAY. Despite the critical acclaim, not all reviews have been positive. The Chicago Tribune called the sequel "pointless," while the New York Post criticized Keaton's performance. However, the film is expected to have a strong opening weekend at the box office, according to Deadline.
